                                                                    <p>Let's talk about something totally different: a powerful part of object-oriented
code called <em>exceptions</em>.</p>
<p>In <code>index.php</code>, we create a <code>BrokenShip</code> object. I'm going to do something crazy,
guys. I'm going to say, <code>$brokenShip-&gt;setStrength()</code> and pass it... <code>banana</code>:</p>
