<p>First, we planned ahead. When we created the <code>setStrength()</code> method, we said:</p>
<blockquote><p>You know what? This needs to be a number, so if somebody passes something
  dumb like "banana," then let's check for that and trigger an error.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Second, in order to trigger an error, we threw an <em>exception</em>. And that's actually
what I want to talk about: Exceptions are classes, but they're completely special.</p>
<p>But first, <code>Exception</code> is a core PHP class, and when we added a <code>namespace</code> to this
file, we forgot to change it to <code>\Exception</code>:</p>
